\section{Inference System (\texttt{model\_inference.py})}
% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The inference module is intentionally decoupled from the UI to ensure the model logic can be tested independently. It exposes two public functions:

\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=1.5em]
  \item \texttt{load\_model(path)} — Rebuilds the MobileNetV2 architecture with the 12-class head and loads the saved \texttt{.pth} weights. Sets model to \texttt{eval()} mode.
  \item \texttt{predict(image, model)} — Applies the inference transform, runs a single forward pass under \texttt{torch.no\_grad()}, applies softmax, and returns \texttt{(class\_name, confidence)}.
\end{itemize}

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={Inference pipeline (model\_inference.py)}]
class_names = [
    "aloo_tikki","bhatura","chana_masala","daal_puri",
    "jalebi","kachori","kuzhi_paniyaram","lassi",
    "litti_chokha","poha","rabri","unni_appam"
]

def predict(image, model):
    image = transform(image).unsqueeze(0)   # shape: [1, 3, 224, 224]
    with torch.no_grad():
        outputs = model(image)
        probs = torch.nn.functional.softmax(outputs, dim=1)
        conf, pred = torch.max(probs, 1)
    return class_names[pred.item()], conf.item()
\end{lstlisting}

\begin{infobox}[Important: Class Order]
The \texttt{class\_names} list in \texttt{model\_inference.py} must exactly match the alphabetical ordering used by \texttt{torchvision.datasets.ImageFolder} during training. Any mismatch will cause silent mis-labelling.
\end{infobox}

